"1267","1144":"1144","1176":"1176","Walcott, Norfolk, , England":"Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Walcot","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Walcott  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Walcott","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of several places called Walcott, Walcot, or Walcote, for example in Lincolnshire, Leicestershire, Norfolk, Oxfordshire, and Wiltshire, all named in Old English <i>walh</i> ‘foreigner, Briton, serf’ (genitive plural <i>wala</i>) + <i>cot</i> ‘cottage, hut, shelter’ (plural <i>cotu</i>), i.e. ‘the cottage where the (Welsh-speaking) Britons lived’. This name is also frequent in Barbados and Jamaica, when emancipated slaves adopted it from the name of one or other of the sugar plantations owned there by English families called Walcott.","History: This surname was in MA from an early date. William Walcott emigrated from England to Salem, MA, in 1637; John Wolcott (1632–1690) is recorded in Springfield, MA."]}]},{"name":"David","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the greatest of all the kings of Israel, whose history is recounted with great vividness in the first and second books of Samuel and elsewhere. As a boy he killed the giant Philistine Goliath with his slingshot. As king of Judah, and later of all Israel, he expanded the power of the Israelites and established the security of their kingdom. He was also noted as a poet, many of the Psalms being attributed to him. The Hebrew derivation of the name is uncertain; it is said by some to represent a nursery word meaning ‘darling’. It is a very popular Jewish name, but is almost equally common among Gentiles in the English-speaking world. It is particularly common in Wales and Scotland, having been borne by the patron saint of Wales (  see  Dewi   ) and by two medieval kings of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. David Walcot was born in 1146, in Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with David Walcot. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1146–":"1146–Surnud","1144–1235":"1144–1235","1176–1267":"1176–1267","1146–Female":"1146–Surnud","1235":"1235","1146":"1146","1267":"1267","1144":"1144","1176":"1176","Walcott, Norfolk, , England":"Walcott, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Walcott, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1146–":"1146–Kuollut","1144–1235":"1144–1235","1176–1267":"1176–1267","1146–Female":"1146–Kuollut","1235":"1235","1146":"1146","1267":"1267","1144":"1144","1176":"1176","Walcott, Norfolk, , England":"Walcott, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Walcott, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1146–":"1146–Décédée","1144–1235":"1144–1235","1176–1267":"1176–1267","1146–Female":"1146–Décédée","1235":"1235","1146":"1146","1267":"1267","1144":"1144","1176":"1176","Walcott, Norfolk, , England":"Walcott, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Walcott, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. David Walcot est née en 1146, à Walcott, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec David Walcot. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1146–":"1146–Verstorben","1144–1235":"1144–1235","1176–1267":"1176–1267","1146–Female":"1146–Verstorben","1235":"1235","1146":"1146","1267":"1267","1144":"1144","1176":"1176","Walcott, Norfolk, , England":"Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mrs. David Walcot wurde 1146 in Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mi